{
  "$schema": "../schemas/Causal-Decision-Model.json",
  "meta": {
    "uuid": "8e8a7b9b-dc3a-47a0-bb0a-7ed028370d46",
    "name": "SKEL-02: Inventory & Stock Management",
    "summary": "Canonical skeleton for inventory and stock management. Four Levers, four Externals, nine Intermediates, three Outcomes. 33 causal dependencies.",
    "documentation": {
      "content": "KODI Lite \u00b7 SKEL-02 \u00b7 Inventory & Stock Management\n\nLevers (4): Reorder Point, Safety Stock Buffer Target, Supplier Contract Terms, Warehouse Capacity Allocation\nExternals (4): Supplier Lead Time Volatility, Market Consumption Rate, Holding Capital Interest Rate, Perishability / Shelf-Life Constraint\nIntermediates (9): Procurement Lag Index [I1 = w1*E1 - w2*A3 + b], Demand Spike Velocity [I2 = (E2[t]-E2[t-1])/dt + b], Storage Space Utilisation [I3 = w1*A2 + w2*I5 - w3*A4 + b], Order Frequency Rate [I4 = w1*A1 + w2*I2 - w3*A3 + b], Cycle Stock [I5 = A3_qty/2 - w1*I2 + b], Available Stock Level [I6 = w1*A2 + w2*I5 - w3*E2 + b], Stockout Risk [I7 = w1*I1 + w2*I2 - w3*A2 + b], Inventory Shrinkage Rate [I8 = w1*A2 - w2*E4 + b], Inventory Turnover Velocity [I9 = w1*E2 - w2*A1 - w3*I8 + b]\nOutcomes (3): Service Level / Fill Rate [maximise], Total Carrying Costs [minimise], Deadstock Overhead [minimise]",
      "MIMEType": "text/plain"
    },
    "version": "1.0",
    "draft": false,
    "createdDate": "2026-07-01T09:00:00Z"
  },
